@startuml seq-revocation
title Credential Revocation Flow

actor "Admin" as admin
participant "Discovery API" as disc
participant "Discovery DB" as db
participant "Vault (Discovery)" as vault
participant "StatusListAnchor\n(Blockchain)" as chain
participant "Producer Sentinel" as psent
participant "Redis (Producer)" as redis

== Admin initiates revocation ==

admin -> disc: POST /api/v1/credentials/<jti>/revoke\n{\n  "reason": "SERVICE_DEREGISTERED"\n}\nAuthorization: Bearer <admin-api-key>

disc -> db: SELECT credentials WHERE jti=<jti> AND status=ACTIVE
db --> disc: credential record\n{ jti, status_list_index=42, status_list_id="list-001" }

disc -> db: SELECT status_lists WHERE id="list-001" FOR UPDATE
db --> disc: { bitstring_bytes, version=17 }

disc -> disc: Set bit 42 → 1 in bitstring

disc -> vault: Read issuer key for status list signing\nsecret/issuers/prod/signing_key
vault --> disc: private_key_bytes

disc -> disc: Build BitstringStatusListCredential JWT-VC\nsign with issuer key
disc -> disc: Compute sha256(new_bitstring)

disc -> chain: statusAnchor.updateHash\n("list-001", new_hash, version+1)
chain --> disc: txHash

disc -> db: UPDATE status_lists\nSET bitstring=<new>, version=18, updated_at=now()\nSET tx_hash=txHash
disc -> db: UPDATE credentials SET status=REVOKED WHERE jti=<jti>
disc -> db: INSERT audit_log\n{ action=VC_REVOKED, target=jti, actor=admin, reason, ts }

disc --> admin: 200 OK\n{\n  "jti": "<jti>",\n  "status": "REVOKED",\n  "effective_at": "ISO8601",\n  "status_list_tx": "<txHash>"\n}

== Producer Sentinel learns about revocation (async, within Δ) ==

note over psent, redis
  Producer Sentinel refreshes the status list cache
  on a schedule (every min(Δ/2, 60s) for prod).
  The next refresh after revocation will pick up the new bit.
end note

psent -> disc: GET /api/v1/status/list-001
disc --> psent: BitstringStatusListCredential JWT-VC

psent -> psent: Verify status list signature
psent -> chain: statusAnchor.getHash("list-001")
chain --> psent: new_hash
psent -> psent: sha256(bitstring) == new_hash ✓

psent -> redis: SET status_list:list-001 <new_bitstring> EX <delta>
redis --> psent: ok

note over psent
  Next request for jti at status_list_index=42
  will find bit=1 → HTTP 403 STATUS_REVOKED
end note

@enduml
